                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1758¼</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">14 May, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My Dear Mr. Secretary: It is hard to turn away from any suggestion that might
                    seem to promise safety for our travellers, but what is suggested seems to me
                    both weak and futile. To show this sort of weak yielding to threat and danger
                    would only make matters worse.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
